## 5. API ENDPOINTS

### Root Endpoint (No Auth Required)
```bash
GET http://localhost:8000/
```
Returns: HTML dashboard

### Authenticated Endpoints (Requires API Key Header)
Default API Key: `default-key-super-secret-12345`

#### Get System Stats
```bash
curl -H "X-API-Key: default-key-super-secret-12345" \
  http://localhost:8000/api/stats
```

#### Upload File
```bash
curl -X POST \
  -H "X-API-Key: default-key-super-secret-12345" \
  -F "file=@/path/to/file.txt" \
  http://localhost:8000/api/send
```

#### List Files
```bash
curl -H "X-API-Key: default-key-super-secret-12345" \
  http://localhost:8000/api/receive
```

#### Download File
```bash
curl -H "X-API-Key: default-key-super-secret-12345" \
  -O \
  http://localhost:8000/api/receive/filename
```

#### Execute Command
```bash
curl -X POST \
  -H "X-API-Key: default-key-super-secret-12345" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"command":"whoami"}' \
  http://localhost:8000/api/execute
```

